11/06/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Interior Minister Hari Kostov and his Montenegrin counterpart, Milan Filipovic, signed a bilateral agreement Tuesday (10 June) on co-operation against organised crime. 
It envisions tightening border controls to prevent the illegal trafficking of drugs, weapons and humans. 
The document also calls for the future exchange of liaison officers.
In other news, the Macedonian Air Forces and Air Defence Forces celebrated their official holiday Tuesday. 
Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski used the occasion to encourage preparations for NATO membership. 
(MIA, Makfax - 10/06/03)
